other_tests.findings: The uterus measures 6.2 x 3.2 x 3.6 cm. An intrauterine device appears within standard position. The ovaries are normal with normal arterial and venous Doppler waveforms. No evidence of ovarian torsion. There is a small amount of free fluid in the pelvis. A tubular structure measuring 5 mm in diameter is at the site of pain, with inconclusive findings possibly indicating a dilated appendix.
